TI  - A decision support system to predict long-term changes in peatland functions
T2  - WETLANDS: MONITORING, MODELLING AND MANAGEMENT
LA  - English
CP  - International Conference Wetlands - Monitoring, Modelling and Management
KW  - WATER
KW  - FLUXES
AB  - For the implementation of sustainable land use strategies in Europe tools for evaluating long-term changes of peatland functions are essential. Therefore a semi-quantitative decision-support system for agricultural used peatlands in Europe (PMDSS) was developed. It is an aiding tool to understand and to forecast long-term processes of peatland ecosystems and is based on the multifunctional concept. Indicators of the peatland functions are: harvest of plant products, land use category, global warming potential, nitrogen discharge, summer water table and conservation value of plants. The PMDSS is developed as an easy to use spreadsheet program. The model is one-dimensional and applicable for a site or field, where the input parameters, particularly land use category, vegetation type and water table are relatively homogenous. The model is running with annual intervals and for a time span of 50-100 years. An application example for a minerotrophic peatland in North-West Germany is described.
